"t_title163","〈台北都會〉《耗資百萬》「海洋熊讚」亮相 挨批好醜
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  〔記者蔡亞樺／台北報導〕台北市政府吉祥物「熊讚」改版後的新造型，昨在花博爭艷館的台灣文博會正式亮相，鼻子變成海洋色、多了兩道短眉，微笑嘴變成噘嘴，與舊版熊讚站在一起，明顯有差異。北市觀光傳播局於臉書進行直播，但網友與熊粉罵聲一片，批評好醜，還有人喊求「還我舊熊讚」，當場落淚。觀傳局長陳思宇表示，雖然外觀有些不同，但精神與活力永遠不變。 觀傳局昨揭開新版海洋熊讚廬山真面目，主持人營造趣味橋段，走上舞台的熊讚頭頂著箱子搞神秘，打開後，還是原本的面孔，台下熊粉歡聲雷動。隨後，舊版熊讚配合主持人演故事，描述在旅途中一處山洞，遇到和自己相似的身影，不過對方鼻子是海洋色的，因此新造型又被暱稱為「海洋熊讚」。 演完故事後，海洋熊讚才現身，新、舊兩熊進行一場交接儀式，接著熱舞，還互相擁抱、作勢親親，最後新版熊讚與台下熊粉送舊版熊讚離去，讓熊粉直呼不捨，氣氛感傷，有人甚至當場落淚，直說很捨不得！ 陳思宇致詞表示，金牌熊讚在另一個世界遇到海洋熊讚，外表有些差異，但個性和靈魂一樣，熊讚永遠是熊讚，期待未來品牌化經營，希望跨足國際，有更多發揮角色。 對於新熊讚，多數網友不買帳，熊讚臉書網友都持負面評價，不少人直呼「（舊版）熊讚不要走」，有網友直言「舊熊讚走了，我要退（粉絲頁）了」，還有網友說，「新熊讚超醜！好瘦醜死了！我要胖胖舊熊讚啊！還我們舊熊讚」。 長期關注藝術與文化的台灣大學語言學研究所教授江文瑜表示，以設計角度來看，新熊讚是否比較可愛，見仁見智，但舊版熊讚的嘴型呈現微笑弧線，眼睛雖有點脫窗，但十分憨厚誠懇，這也是許多粉絲喜歡熊讚的原因。 江文瑜說，舊版熊讚帶領大家走過世大運的歡笑淚水，升格成了市府吉祥物，參加推廣台北公益活動，充滿正面能量，並走出台北關懷偏遠孩童，大家喜歡熊讚是透過一點一滴的記憶，與民眾最深刻的情感連結，觀傳局卻堅持改版，市長柯文哲竟也沒阻止，令人意外，她呼籲市府保留舊版熊讚。 陳思宇說，這次改版包括玩偶、文字與2D圖檔都結合台北精神，熊讚代表台北的精神，未來熊讚仍會以公益、市政宣傳為主，不會參加任何選舉活動。先前稱舊版不再亮相，但陳昨改口，若時空出現裂痕，在等時機點，兩隻熊讚可能會一起出席活動。 台北市政府吉祥物「熊讚」新造型亮相，左邊是舊的熊讚，右邊是新的「海洋熊讚」。（記者蔡亞樺攝） 熊讚改版事件簿 新聞送上來！快加入自由電子報APP、LINE好友  2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅 注目新聞 1 中國卡車罷工延燒 司機高喊「打倒共產黨」！ 2 新版身分證票選出爐 設計師魯少綸奪首獎！ 3 洋腸又來！夜店外帶18歲妹 網站取名「台女很容易」... 4 侯友宜妻1塊土地99個門牌 蘇貞昌：太荒唐 5 連俞涵超正弟媳曝光…根本巨乳林志玲！","153"
"t_title164","《TAIPEI TIMES》 KMT hopefuls debate plans for Taipei
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  CULTURAL CAPITAL: The four aspirants agreed on expanding exchanges with China and resolving the Taipei Dome issue, but were divided regarding Songshan airport By Stacy Hsu / Staff reporter Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） Taipei mayoral candidate hopefuls yesterday called for closer exchanges with China and the “reinvigoration of Chinese culture” to boost the capital’s economy and tourism, and laid out plans for the Taipei International Airport （Songshan airport） and Taipei Dome projects. The proposals were made at the first televised debate for the KMT’s four aspirants: Taipei City Councilor Chung Hsiao-ping （鍾小平）, former Mainland Affairs Council deputy minister Chang Hsien-yao （張顯耀） and former KMT legislators Ting Shou-chung （丁守中） and Sun Ta-chien （孫大千）. The debate, organized and aired by CtiTV, came the week before the KMT headquarters is scheduled to conduct a telephone poll from Sunday next week to May 1 to decide its candidate. A focus of the debate was the annual twin-city forum, which has been held in Taipei and Shanghai on a rotating basis since 2010 to promote exchanges between the cities. There have been allegations that Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je （柯文哲）, who is seeking re-election, has decided to postpone this year’s forum in Taipei until after the election due to political concerns. “At a time when President Tsai Ing-wen’s （蔡英文） and Premier William Lai’s （賴清德） political stances have caused cross-strait relations to stall and have led to frequent Chinese military drills, the need to strengthen exchanges at the local level has grown even greater,” Ting said. If elected, Ting said he would push for a similar twin-city forum with other major Chinese cities, such as Beijing and Shenzhen, as well as cities in other nations that provide Taiwan and Taipei with good business opportunities. Chang agreed, but also proposed establishing city-level representative offices in Chinese cities with a large number of Taiwanese businesspeople, while Sun pledged to make sure that the annual forum yields achievements not only in politics, but also in culture and innovation. Regarding tourism, Chung said that the city should make the best of the National Palace Museum and its rich collection of ancient Chinese artifacts and art, instead of pursuing a “desinicization” movement. “Chinese fever is everywhere around the world — why would anyone still want to pursue desinicization? We must reinvigorate the 5,000-year-old Chinese culture here, because that is our most valuable appeal,” Chung said. All four hopefuls vowed to put a swift end to the scandal surrounding the Taipei Dome, the construction of which has been suspended for more than two years due to safety concerns. Ting said he would complete the project as soon as possible, while Chang said he would make a decision within three months of his election on whether to tear down, resume construction or redesign the dome. While Chung said he plans to terminate the contract between the Taipei City Government and Farglory Group and start new negotiations, Sun said that the dome’s fate should be determined by the contract. The four were divided on Songshan airport, with Chung and Chang advocating for its immediate relocation to allow further development of the neighboring areas, and Ting and Sun saying that such a move would not be possible until after a third terminal is built at Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport. 新聞來源：TAIPEI TIMES Former Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） legislators Ting Shou-chung, left, and Sun Ta-chien, second left, KMT Taipei City Councilor Chung Hsiao-ping, second right, and former Mainland Affairs Council deputy minister Chang Hsien-yao yesterday participate in the first televised debate between the party’s Taipei mayoral candidate hopefuls.
